Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
specifyScanCell(25.10)                                  specifyScanCell(25.10)

Name
       specifyScanCell  - Specifies scan cells that are not listed in the tim-
       ing library

Syntax
       specifyScanCell

       [-help]

       <[><cellName>]

       [-in <ftname>]

       [-out <ftname>]

       [-scanClock <ftname>]

       [-scanEnable <ftname>]

       Specifies scan cells that are not listed in the timing library.

Parameters
       <cellName>
              Specifies name of the scan cell.

       -in <ftname>
              Specifies the name of the scan input.

       -out <ftname>
              Specifies the name of the scan output.

       -scanClock <ftname>
              Specifies the name of the scan clock.

       -scanEnable <ftname>
              Specifies name of the scan enable f-term or pin names.

Example
       The following command specifies cell SDFFQ to be a scan cell:

       specifyScanCell SDFFQ -in SI -out Q

